snippet.title: Humko Tum Mil Gaye - Naresh Sharma ft.Vishal Mishra | Hina Khan, Dheeraj Dhoopar | Sayeed Q|New Song
snippet.description:
VYRL Originals presents Naresh Sharma‚Äôs Humko Tum Mil Gaye. A soulful romantic ballad sung by the mesmerising Vishal Mishra and the words beautifully penned by Sayeed Quadri. Watch Hina Khan and Dheeraj Dhoopar, (TV‚Äôs Most adored couple from the fame of Naagin 5) in this music video as they portray a journey of a couple's undying love & resilience. A song which will remind you that appreciation is an emotion which we seldom express to our loved ones and there is no greater feeling that to live this emotion everyday.

snippet.title: 28 CLEVER CAMPING IDEAS || DIY TRAVEL HACKS TO HELP YOU ON A TRIP
snippet.description:
Brilliant outdoor ideas for adventure lovers

If you can't imagine yourself staying at home every weekend and would rather be lost somewhere in a wild forest, then these camping life hacks are for you! Our collection of smart travel tips and road ideas will definitely help you solve any problem while you're away from home on another adventure.

You don't need to buy a boat if you need one. Instead, try out our recycling DIY ideas - making a boat yourself by reusing a big old plastic bottle. Take a bottle of a size where you can comfortably sit in and cut a hole in it. Attach pool noodles as a safe edging around the cut and fix some wooden planks. They will help you balance the weight in a boat. Take a paddle and you're ready for a new river or lake adventure! Be sure to always wear a life west for safety during your trip üõ∂

You may not take a bucket on your trips, but always take an adhesive tape, because you can DIY almost anything with it, for example, a bucket. Fins a big tree branch and place a plastic bag on it. Now tape it all around with an adhesive tape creating the shape of the bag. The tape bucket is more durable than a plastic bag, you can use it for carrying water or any other goods.

snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to SAB TV Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/sabtv?sub_confirmation=1

Click to watch all the episodes of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6Rtnh6YJK7Zfu1x9Bd1UqLwUxhZ1oBJh

The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in """"Gokuldham Co-operative Society"""" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - Promoolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

snippet.description:

In this video we are exploring the school life. Madam hurts the very tangible ego of Leelu Pradhan and he decided to take over the school as Leelu MasterJI. Leelu enters the school as a teacher and becomes students favourite teacher. Jealous of Leelu's fame, Raseelu also decided to go to school as Sanskrit teacher. Leelu and Raseelu saw each other in school and starts questioning each others presence. Then we see Bakhtawar also roaming in the school as GK teacher. Now all three of them are in school creating confusion everywhere. Video is filled with funny moments of school life.
Let's wait for episode 2 of this video where we are dealing with the important issues of students. Video takes emotional turn in second episode when Leelu discovers how students are suffering in current education system. At the end story ends with a laughter.
This series is filled with school life moments, students teachers jokes, love, friendship etc. It will make you feel nostalgic about your school life.

snippet.title: Mere Yaar - N-Gritz Feat. Sarang Sikander | YJKD Season 2 - 30th Sept | Latest Punjabi Song 2020
snippet.description:
Exactly two Years ago, Troll Punjabi Came out with Punjab's First web series "Yaar Jigree Kasooti Degree". And, after huge sucess of the first season, we are all set to bring you the first Promotional song "Mere Yaar" from Free Fire presents "Yaar Jigri Kasuti Degree Season 2". First Episode of the much-awaited new season is all set to premiere on 30th September on Troll Punjabi.

Season 1 of Yaar Jigri Kasooti Degree ended in total chaos. Events unfolded in such a way that our beloved characters were set on different paths and were separated from each other. Jass and Ekam were left alone and without a roof. Lucky's actions ended him in jail and where he awaits his fate. Heartbroken Roop felt guilty for what he has done to people close to him. Uncertain of his future, Anmol has to give up all his dreams and returned home. 


Written & Directed by Rabby Tiwana
Starring : Pukhraj Bhalla, Prateek Singh Rai, Sukhdeep Sapra, Karan Sandhawalia, Karanvir Deol 
Singer: N-Gritz Feat Sarang Sikander 
(Insta : sarangsikander786) 
Music: JT Beats (Insta : beatsbybhatti) 
Lyrics: N-Gritz (Insta : iamngritz) 
Mix Mastering: Alaap Sikander (Insta : alaapsikander) 
Cinematography: Gagan Sarao
Editing: Rabby Tiwana & Gursimran Thind
Colourist: Prince K Makkar
Poster Design: Mehnge Bande
Co-Actors: Sukhi Patran, Babar Khan, Chamkour Billa, Dilveer Dill, Satnam Dhuri

Recreated from 
Precious Moments Feat. Ngritz and Lovepreet Sandhu.. Released in August 2011

YJKD Season 2 Crew:
Directed by Rabby Tiwana
(Email - rabby@trollpunjabi.com, Contact No. +919569453006)
Cinematography: Gagan Sarao
Co-writers: Bhindi Tolawal, Paramveer Sharma & Angad Sadana
Dialogues: Bhindi Tolawal
Executive Producer: Sukhjinder Singh
Chief AD: Angad Sadana
Asst. Director: Mohit Kapoor
2nd AD: Mohit Wadhwa 
Camera Assistants: Karan Kamra, Parvesh Sharma, Baldeep Singh Sidhu
Casting Director: Sukhchain Singh
Sound Recordist : Ram Sohi
Set Designers : Gurkirat Virk, Laddi Sangtiwala 
Costume Designer: Avinash Shukla
Gaffer: Manpreet Singh (Larry)
Production Manager: Amrinder Laddi , Daya Virk
Makeup & Hair: Harwinder Harry

Follow us on Insta - https://www.instagram.com/troll_punjabi/
Snapchat - troll-punjabi

Song Lyrics -
Yaad aunde ne oh saal,vakhri sigi chaal,
College de c o din katte c yaaran naal,
kiven c ande jaande,kiven kudi ptaunde,
kiven gandasse chak vairiyan naa(naal) vair nbhaunde

bhul diyan ni raatan naal btayiyan jedi,
sukh ya dukh hove sige hamesha ready,
rabba tu das ve tu kalla kyun chadeya,
sinne cho dil kad tainu ki ae milya??????????

bhul ni pavanga mai oh saare lamhe,
dukh ne jede aj karde tang ne,
akha vich athru ni oh sarre bharge,
jede c naal aj dur kithe chalge,

hundi ni baardaash mere to ne hun duriyan,
zindgi boj ban gayi ae majbooriyan
likh ke geet aj zindagi mai khojda
kiven kar javan os pal ch mai sochda..

Ik-ik gal jediiiiii yaaran naal kitti aj baike mai oh gal sochdan
Ik-ik khushi jediiii ohne ne ditti band kamre baike aj khojdan
Rabba das de kithe ne o saare mere yaar X2

Tusi ta sige jine pehlan c plai mainu,
Tusi c jine pehli kudi c ptai mainu,
Tusi c jinne pehlan stage te chadaya mainu
Tusi ta sige jitho dillo pyaar aya mainu

Jdo c lod mainu sare marij c,
yaar hi c mere jinaaa likhi taqdeer c,
rabba maaf kari naaaa bura tu man ji,
mai tainu bhul ju par yaari ni bhul ni,

maafi mangda, jinna to naio mang paya,
aj labdaa ohnanuuu jinne jinna sakhaya,
yaarian na rabba kade kisse di dur kari,
jede vichde c aj ona da v mel kari,

yarri nu salaam jinne saath nabhaya,
naal mere khad es makaaam te punchaya,
ik ik kar hun jana mai ohna kol,
jina ne bnayi meri zindagi anmol..

Ik-2 gal jediiiiii ... X2

Chal paya mai os raah jithe yaar mere 
Labh ni paa reha mai jhere riste c gehre
Socha vich pya mai kive dikhava mukh
Hor vi ni chara jitho mainu miluga sukh
Hun na tu roki rabba ehi ardaas meri
Jann layi tu himmat davi aahi umeed meri
Raah vich je digeya ta tuhi sambhal li
Par kise na kise tu othe pohncha di 
Jithe rehnde yaar mere dilo dildaar mere
Akhan de sukh ne oh ohi ne pyaar mere
Akhan ne bhariya ne hun rabb gawah ehda
Athru mithaun yaar aahi khwaab mera
Poora bharosa nale yakeen v
Yaar jad milu hou dastan haseen g
Jaan ge russ oh galat v kehn ge
Par maaf kar mainu gal naal v rehn 
Ik-2 gal jediiiiii ..... X2

The Denver Nuggets made NBA history last night becoming the first team to ever come back and win a series down 3-1 twice in the same postseason. Kawhi Leonard, who went 6 of 22 from the floor for 14 points, and the Los Angeles Clippers were left stunned as their championship aspirations were cut short of even a conference finals appearance. Paul George didn‚Äôt help matters with only 10 points on 4 of 16 shooting last night. Hear what Skip Bayless and Shannon Sharpe have to say about the Nuggets' shocking upset.

snippet.title: The Real Reason Cardi B Filed For Divorce
snippet.description:
From Making Up To Breaking Up It Looks Like These Two Are Done For Good
Subscribe: http://bit.ly/Subscribe-to-Talko
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Cardi B has filed divorce from the Migos rapper, Offset after three years of marriage. 2020 has been a rollercoaster with everything that has been happening. It just keeps giving us more. That more came from Cardi B calling it quits in her marriage with Offset, citing cheating as the reason. She is seeking sole custody of their daughter, Kulture. The hearing is set for November 4th. To many it was a surprise but Cardi has been hinting at the split the past few months.
 
Individually, they are both accomplished artists in hip hop, making the two a power couple. Cardi B and Offset‚Äôs romance began back in 2017. They collaborated on Cardi B‚Äôs song Lick before making it official on Instagram. They moved very fast and were married secretly by September of that year. Soon there was trouble in paradise as Offset was accused of cheating. A video made rounds on social media and Cardi confirmed the rumours herself in an interview with Cosmopolitan. She forgave him but the rumours didn‚Äôt stop. Up until her filing for divorce, there was always speculation. Ultimately, infidelity was the reason Cardi filed for divorce.
 
As we wait for the court hearing, let us know your opinions about their relationship. Do you think they will stay separated this time? Will Cardi be able to get sole custody? Follow us so you can stay up-to-date with the latest in their news and pop culture. Subscribe to our Youtube channel, The Talko, and don‚Äôt forget to turn on notifications!

snippet.title: Chris Broussard concedes to Wright after Clippers lose to Denver in GM 7 | NBA | FIRST THINGS FIRST
snippet.description:
Chris Broussard joins the show to discuss the devastating loss of the Los Angeles Clippers to the Denver Nuggets in Game 7 of the semifinals during NBA playoffs in the Orlando bubble. Broussard finally concedes to Nick Wright, admitting he thought the Clippers were the best in league when they clearly could not deliver. However, Broussard feels they will be humbled next season and finally be ready for a championship.

snippet.title: iOS 14 Official Review!
snippet.description:
iOS 14 Official Review! Hello all and welcome to this official review of iOS 14. In this episode we will breakdown the entire iOS 14 update and help you understand all the new features that you will be getting with this iOS update for your smartphone. The intentions of this video is to equip you with the knowledge you need about the new iOS 14 features to help you better use the new software. Apple iOS 14 is available for all phones that ran iOS 13 including phones such as iPhone 6S. Apple iOS 14 features some neat features like App library, All new widget interface, updates to Apple health, voice memos, maps, siri, carplay, and much more. If you have downloaded iOS 14, please consider sharing your experiences with the community down below in the comment section of this video and anything that I might have missed in this video :) As always, thank you for watching and be sure to well and peace.

#iOS14 #iOS14features #iOS14official #Apple2020 #iPhone #software #iphoneiOS14 #appleevent #iphone12

snippet.title: How Kodak Detected the Atomic Bomb
snippet.description:
Kodak detected the first atomic bomb before anyone else figured it out. Then they made a deal not to tell anyone. Thanks to HBO Max, and their new show raised by Wolves for sponsoring this video! https://rb.gy/alghwn

References:
Albuquerque Tribune Bulletin, July 16, 1945 ‚Äì https://www.marshallfoundation.org/library/documents/albuquerque-tribune-bulletin-16-july-1945/

Webb, J. H. (1949). The fogging of photographic film by radioactive contaminants in cardboard packaging materials. Physical Review, 76(3), 375.

Julian Webb at Oak Ridge ‚Äì Snavely, B. B. (1989). Julian H. Webb. PhT, 42(7), 87.https://physicstoday.scitation.org/doi/pdf/10.1063/1.2811100

Radium in watch dials ‚Äì https://www.epa.gov/radtown/radioactivity-antiques

A 1958 video about how Kodak film is made, noting the careful monitoring of radioactive contaminants ‚Äì https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9qjBJOFImaU&t=597s&ab_channel=OwenMorgan

Radioactive fallout in 1951 - https://www.nytimes.com/1951/02/03/archives/increased-radiation-found-in-east-laid-to-atom-tests-held-harmless.html?searchResultPosition=20

1998 senate hearing ‚Äì https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/CHRG-105shrg44045/html/CHRG-105shrg44045.htm

Institute of Medicine and National Research Council. 1999. Exposure of the American People to Iodine-131 from Nevada Nuclear-Bomb Tests: Review of the National Cancer Institute Report and Public Health Implications. Washington, DC: The National Academies Press. https://doi.org/10.17226/6283. https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/causes-prevention/risk/radiation/i131-report-and-appendix

Baby Teeth Survey ‚Äì Reiss, L. Z. (1961). Strontium-90 absorption by deciduous teeth. Science, 134(3491), 1669-1673.

Strontium 90 and Cancer rates ‚Äì Gould, J. M., Sternglass, E. J., Sherman, J. D., Brown, J., McDonnell, W., & Mangano, J. J. (2000). Strontium-90 in deciduous teeth as a factor in early childhood cancer. International Journal of Health Services, 30(3), 515-539.

Wine forensics ‚Äì Hubert, P., Perrot, F., Gaye, J., M√©dina, B., & Pravikoff, M. S. (2009). Radioactivity measurements applied to the dating and authentication of old wines. Comptes Rendus Physique, 10(7), 622‚Äì629. doi:10.1016/j.crhy.2009.08.007

Strontium 90 in forensics ‚Äì Maclaughlin-Black, S. M., Herd, R. J., Willson, K., Myers, M., & West, I. E. (1992). Strontium-90 as an indicator of time since death: a pilot investigation. Forensic science international, 57(1), 51-56.

Research and Writing by Derek Muller, Petr Lebedev, and Jonny Hyman

Filmed and edited by Derek Muller
Animations by Iv√°n Tello and Jonny Hyman
Music by Jonny Hyman
Additional Music from: 
Epidemic Sound https://epidemicsound.com "Seaweed"
Kevin MacLeod https://incompetech.com "Lightless dawn"
Craig Conrad https://www.craigconard.com/royaltyfree "ASTRAL"

snippet.title: iOS 14 is Out! - What's New?

In this video I go over all the major changes, updates and features of iOS 14 including some you might not know exist.  Apple also released watchOS 7, iPadOS 14, and tvOS 14 today.  macOS Big Sur look sto be releasing in October around when iPhone 12 is coming.  #ios14 #iOS14 #iPadOS14 #iPhone #apple

snippet.title: Clippers losing GM 7 to Nuggets is the 'biggest choke in NBA history' ‚Äî Shannon | NBA | UNDISPUTED
snippet.description:
The Denver Nuggets made NBA history last night becoming the first team to ever come back and win a series down 3-1 twice in the same postseason. Kawhi Leonard, who went 6 of 22 from the floor for 14 points, and the Los Angeles Clippers were left stunned as their championship aspirations were cut short of even a conference finals appearance. Paul George didn‚Äôt help matters with only 10 points on 4 of 16 shooting last night. Hear what Skip Bayless and Shannon Sharpe have to say about the Nuggets' shocking upset.

snippet.title: How Kodak Detected the Atomic Bomb
snippet.description:
Kodak detected the first atomic bomb before anyone else figured it out. Then they made a deal not to tell anyone. Thanks to HBO Max, and their new show raised by Wolves for sponsoring this video! https://rb.gy/alghwn

References:
Albuquerque Tribune Bulletin, July 16, 1945 ‚Äì https://www.marshallfoundation.org/library/documents/albuquerque-tribune-bulletin-16-july-1945/

Webb, J. H. (1949). The fogging of photographic film by radioactive contaminants in cardboard packaging materials. Physical Review, 76(3), 375.

Julian Webb at Oak Ridge ‚Äì Snavely, B. B. (1989). Julian H. Webb. PhT, 42(7), 87.https://physicstoday.scitation.org/doi/pdf/10.1063/1.2811100

Radium in watch dials ‚Äì https://www.epa.gov/radtown/radioactivity-antiques

A 1958 video about how Kodak film is made, noting the careful monitoring of radioactive contaminants ‚Äì https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9qjBJOFImaU&t=597s&ab_channel=OwenMorgan

Radioactive fallout in 1951 - https://www.nytimes.com/1951/02/03/archives/increased-radiation-found-in-east-laid-to-atom-tests-held-harmless.html?searchResultPosition=20

1998 senate hearing ‚Äì https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/CHRG-105shrg44045/html/CHRG-105shrg44045.htm

Institute of Medicine and National Research Council. 1999. Exposure of the American People to Iodine-131 from Nevada Nuclear-Bomb Tests: Review of the National Cancer Institute Report and Public Health Implications. Washington, DC: The National Academies Press. https://doi.org/10.17226/6283. https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/causes-prevention/risk/radiation/i131-report-and-appendix

Baby Teeth Survey ‚Äì Reiss, L. Z. (1961). Strontium-90 absorption by deciduous teeth. Science, 134(3491), 1669-1673.

Strontium 90 and Cancer rates ‚Äì Gould, J. M., Sternglass, E. J., Sherman, J. D., Brown, J., McDonnell, W., & Mangano, J. J. (2000). Strontium-90 in deciduous teeth as a factor in early childhood cancer. International Journal of Health Services, 30(3), 515-539.

Wine forensics ‚Äì Hubert, P., Perrot, F., Gaye, J., M√©dina, B., & Pravikoff, M. S. (2009). Radioactivity measurements applied to the dating and authentication of old wines. Comptes Rendus Physique, 10(7), 622‚Äì629. doi:10.1016/j.crhy.2009.08.007

Strontium 90 in forensics ‚Äì Maclaughlin-Black, S. M., Herd, R. J., Willson, K., Myers, M., & West, I. E. (1992). Strontium-90 as an indicator of time since death: a pilot investigation. Forensic science international, 57(1), 51-56.

Research and Writing by Derek Muller, Petr Lebedev, and Jonny Hyman

Filmed and edited by Derek Muller
Animations by Iv√°n Tello and Jonny Hyman
Music by Jonny Hyman
Additional Music from: 
Epidemic Sound https://epidemicsound.com "Seaweed"
Kevin MacLeod https://incompetech.com "Lightless dawn"
Craig Conrad https://www.craigconard.com/royaltyfree "ASTRAL"

snippet.title: Prime Minister's Questions: 16 September 2020
snippet.description:
Prime Minister's Question Time, also referred to as PMQs, takes place every Wednesday the House of Commons sits. It gives MPs the chance to put questions to the Prime Minister.

In most cases, the session starts with a routine 'open question' from an MP about the Prime Minister's engagements. MPs can then ask supplementary questions on any subject, often one of current political significance.

Angela Rayner MP, deputy Leader of the Labour Party, asks six questions and the leader of the second largest opposition party asks two. 

Follow https://twitter.com/HouseofCommons for official news and information from the UK House of Commons Chamber.

snippet.title: WHO HAS HAD THE BEST TRANSFER WINDOW SO FAR? | A Tenner Says | 888sport
snippet.description:
The A Tenner Says panel is back to discuss the transfer window and who has been the signing of the summer so far.

With Chelsea splashing the cash on the likes of Werner, Havertz and Thiago Silva, Blues Fans TV star Rory Jennings is convinced the west London club has assembled a Premier League title-winning squad.

But with Arsenal making some shrewd defensive acquisitions, as well as adding winger Willian to their ranks, Tottenham fan Expressions Oozing is concerned the Gunners are on the up.

With Gareth Bale seemingly on the brink of a stunning move back to Spurs, as well as Real Madrid left back Sergio Reguilon, the Lilywhites could yet have an incredible window as they look to get back into the Champions League.

Liverpool fan James Redmond insists the Reds' lack of activity in the market won't count against their title defence, while Steven McInerney - AKA Esteemed Kompany - remains confident in Manchester City's ability to attract the world's best.

The panel also name their signing of the summer, with a couple of shouts for Manchester United's Donny van de Beek.

Who do you think has been the signing of the summer? Let us know in the COMMENTS and don't forget to SUBSCRIBE for weekly content!

Much appreciations to everyone for watching for the past 5 years, TPM is kinda back in full swing, so every fortnight there'll be an episode. I have some sick ideas I might experiment with on the channel, but you could at least guarantee that I'll provide the poultry content you've all come here for. snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Fulham vs Arsenal (0-3) | Willian, Gabriel impress on debuts
snippet.description:
We got off to a flying start in the Premier League with a classy performance and three points at Craven Cottage.

Alex Lacazette, debutant Gabriel and Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang were on target while the outstanding Willian claimed two assists on his first appearance for us.

Fulham were bright in the opening moments and a misjudgement from Gabriel almost let in Aboubakar Kamara. Bernd Leno did well to claw the ball off his toes.

From then on, the home side could not live with our pace, movement and quality.

The first goal was a scrappy one. Mohamed Elneny found Aubameyang and his cutback was fired goalwards by Granit Xhaka. Tim Ream failed to clear, Willian reacted first to force a save from Marek Rodak and Lacazette tucked away the rebound.

Willian struck a free-kick against the base of a post with Rodak beaten, and Aubameyang almost scored from a trademark burst in behind the defence in the left-hand channel.

Gabriel grew in stature as the game unfolded and he marked his debut with a downward header to convert Willian's corner. That effectively put the match to bed very early in the second half.

After that it was a matter of how many we would score, and Aubameyang got the third and final goal thanks to a delightful crossfield pass from Willian and one of the captain's sumptuous finishes into the far corner.

There will be tougher tests ahead, but this was a hugely-encouraging start to the new campaign.

#arsenal #arsenalhighlights #willian #aubameyang #gabrielMagalhaes

This is the Official YouTube channel for Arsenal Football Club. This channel will aim to showcase the personality of Arsenal Football Club and give fans more of an insight into what it's like to be at this fantastic club. This channel will look behind the scenes and get closer to the likes of Mesut Ozil, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, David Luiz, Nicolas Pepe, Alexandre Lacazette, Mesut Ozil, Bernd Leno, Granit Xhaka, Hector Bellerin, Bukayo Saka, Gabriel Martinelli, Bukayo and more.

ABOUT ARSENAL FC


Arsenal Football Club were formed in 1886. They have amassed 13 League titles, 14 FA Cups and many other major trophies since then. Their greatest players include: Thierry Henry, Dennis Bergkamp, Tony Adams, Ian Wright, Robert Pires, Liam Brady, Patrick Vieira, Cliff Bastin and Charlie George.

After that it was a matter of how many we would score, and Aubameyang got the third and final goal thanks to a delightful crossfield pass from Willian and one of the captain's sumptuous finishes into the far corner.

There will be tougher tests ahead, but this was a hugely-encouraging start to the new campaign.

snippet.title: Halal Food Recommended By Our Exes!
snippet.description:
In today's Food King Episode, our hosts go on a hunt to find the best halal dishes in Singapore! We've got halal ramen, Nasi Padang from Padang itself, and one of the best mee rebus we've ever tasted! This is halal food like we've never seen before!

1. Rumah Makan Minang 2:00
18 & 18A Kandahar Street, 198884
Opening hours: 8:30am - 7:30pm daily

Dishes:
- Ikan Bakar - $7.00
- Ayam Bakar Gulai - $3.50 ~ $4.00
- Sotong Masak Hitam - $7.00
- Lemak Pucuk Ubi - $4.50
- Ayam Belado Hijau - $3.50 ~ $4.50
- Beef Rendang - $4.00
- Ikan Asam Pedas 2pcs - $8.00
- Sayur Lemak Lodeh - $4.50
- Indonesian Tahu Telor - $7.00
- Teh Tarik ($1.30 Hot, $2 Cold)

2. Noosh Noodle Bar and Grill 7:21
8 Raffles Ave, #01-13B Esplanade Mall, Singapore 039802
Opening hours: 12 - 10pm daily

Dishes:
- Dome Filet Mignon Surf & Turf $38.90
- Smoked Duck Lemak Chilli Padi Spaghetti $18.90
- Niboshi Ramen with Sliced Beef $21.90
- Butterbeer $10.90 

3. Rahim Muslim Food 12:37
Blk 453A Ang Mo Kio Ave 10
Chong Boon Market, #01-01, Singapore 560453
Opening hours: 12:30 - 7pm, Mon - Sat

Dishes:
- Normal Mee Soto ($4.50)
- Power Mee Rebus ($4.50)

snippet.title: MAX - Blueberry Eyes (feat. SUGA of BTS) [Official Music Video]
snippet.description:
MAX ‚Äì Blueberry Eyes (feat. SUGA of BTS) [Official Music Video]

Stream: https://orcd.co/blueberryeyes 
Spotify: http://open.spotify.com/album/2dEJHnsuxIij7YeBbt0sVm
Apple: https://music.apple.com/us/album/colour-vision/1524457751?ls=1

Bringing this music video to life has been such a special experience. I wanted it to feel as if Disney magically made a baby with Wes Anderson in the world of Colour Vision with every bit of our souls intertwined. Emily is my actual wife and she is really pregnant right now with our first child, so art imitates life in a fun way with this video. We studied and memorized all of the Korean lyrics to Suga‚Äôs incredible and romantic verse and all of the blueberries in the bathtub ended up being reused to create limited edition blueberry dyed blueberry eyes shirts. This video is a piece of our hearts and I hope it sparks the same magic in you viewing it as it did for us creating it. Thank you to Suga for being so brilliant on this song and more importantly for being a wonderful friend. Much love.
-MAX 

Follow MAX 
Website - http://maxmusicofficial.com/
Merch: https://maxofficialmerch.com/
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/maxmusic/
Twitter: https://twitter.com/maxmusic
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/maxmusic
Soundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/officialmaxmusic

Head on my chest
My heart‚Äôs beating
I can‚Äôt wait to

(Chorus)
Kiss you each morning 
With strawberry skies 
I get so lost in 
Your blueberry eyes 
I‚Äôm running through my dreams 
To see you in the light 
Cause I get so lost in 
Your blueberry eyes 

(Verse 2) SUGA

snippet.title: Dune Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Beyond fear, destiny awaits. Watch the trailer for the highly anticipated #DuneMovie now. 


-----------------
https://www.facebook.com/dune
 https://twitter.com/dunemovie
https://www.instagram.com/dunemovie
-----------------

Oscar  nominee  Denis  Villeneuve  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049‚Äù)  directs  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary Pictures‚Äô ‚ÄúDune,‚Äù the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people.  As  malevolent  forces  explode  into conflict over the planet‚Äôs exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence‚Äîa commodity capable of unlocking humanity‚Äôs greatest potential‚Äîonly those who can conquer their fear will survive.The film stars Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name,‚Äù  ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson  (‚ÄúStephen  King‚Äôs  Doctor  Sleep,‚Äù   ‚ÄúMission:  Impossible  ‚Äì  Fallout‚Äù),  Oscar  Isaac  (the ‚ÄúStar  Wars‚Äù franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúMilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Infinity War‚Äù), Stellan Skarsg√•rd (HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúChernobyl,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Endgame‚Äù), Stephen McKinley Henderson (‚ÄúFences,‚Äù ‚ÄúLady Bird‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Chang Chen (‚ÄúMr.  Long,‚Äù ‚ÄúCrouching  Tiger,  Hidden  Dragon‚Äù),    David  Dastmalchian  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Dark  Knight‚Äù), Sharon  Duncan-Brewster  (‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story,‚Äù  Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúSex  Education‚Äù),   with  Oscar  nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), with Jason Momoa (‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúGame of Thrones‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúSkyfall‚Äù).   Villeneuve directed ‚ÄúDune‚Äù from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert.  Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter  and  Joe  Caracciolo,  Jr.   The  executive  producers  are  Tanya  Lapointe,  Joshua  Grode,  Herbert  W.  Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert. Behind  the  scenes,  Villeneuve  reteamed  with  two-time  Oscar-nominated  production  designer  Patrice  Vermette  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúSicario,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Young  Victoria‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-nominated  editor  Joe  Walker  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚Äú12  Years  a  Slave‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-winning  visual  effects  supervisor  Paul  Lambert  (‚ÄúFirst Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù).    He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù  ‚ÄúZero  Dark  Thirty,‚Äù  ‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story‚Äù);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  
Jacqueline West (‚ÄúThe Revenant,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,‚Äù ‚ÄúQuills‚Äù) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúInception‚Äù).  Oscar-winning and multiple  Oscar-nominated  composer  Hans  Zimmer  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúInception,‚Äù  ‚ÄúGladiator,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Lion King‚Äù) is creating the score.  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary  Pictures  Present  ‚ÄúDune.‚Äù    The  film  is  slated  to  be  released  in  theaters on December 18, 2020.

snippet.title: Street Food FRIED CHICKEN!! üçó The Ultimate Thai Fried Chicken Tour!! | Hat Yai, Thailand
snippet.description:
üé• Chiang Mai Street Food Tour: https://youtu.be/2hV2MQpTdCg
üëç 100% Durian Chips - Order Here: http://pixelfy.me/uY4K5z

Welcome to Hat Yai (‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà), the biggest city in Southern Thailand and one of the biggest cities in Thailand. It was my first time to visit and I was thrilled to have a chance to explore the amazing food and mix of cultures. But of all the delicious street food in Hat Yai, there‚Äôs nothing more famous than Hat Yai Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà). Get ready for an ultimate fried chicken street food tour! #HatYai #Thailand #streetfood #friedchicken

When you mention fried chicken in Thailand, immediately people from the entire country will think about Hat Yai, and you can find Hat Yai style Thai fried chicken in pretty much every town and village throughout Thailand. There are a couple things to first know about this style of fried chicken. Number one is that it‚Äôs usually a very light batter - not bready. The marinade often includes some Thai spices like coriander seed and roots, pepper, and sometimes milk. The chicken is fried so all the golden crispiness is coating the meat rather than on the breading. Next, Hat Yai Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà) is almost always eaten with sticky rice. Finally, it would not be Hat Yai Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà) without crispy fried shallots. That combination is what makes it what it is, and it‚Äôs crazy good.

Here are the places we ate:

Laila Fried Chicken (‡∏£‡πâ‡∏≤‡∏ô‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡πÑ‡∏•‡∏•‡∏≤) - https://goo.gl/maps/xHiCisnySpvCXaKP8 - First we headed to this amazing street food stall for popular fried chicken, especially catering to students from the Prince of Songkhla University. Fried chicken was excellent, and they are extremely friendly.

Ba Sao Fried Chicken (‡∏õ‡πâ‡∏≤‡∏™‡∏≤‡∏ß‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡πÑ‡∏°‡πâ‡∏ü‡∏∑‡∏ô) - https://goo.gl/maps/akeF6xsgRYyYdDut8 - What‚Äôs especially cool about this old school fried chicken stall is they still cook over wood fire. The chicken is crispy and delicious.

Kaitod MEENA (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà‡∏°‡∏µ‡∏ô‡∏≤) - https://g.page/KaitodMeena?share - Located right at the main market in Hat Yai. I loved the biryani with fried chicken, and the owners are so friendly.

Welcome to Hat Yai (‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà), the biggest city in Southern Thailand and one of the biggest cities in Thailand. It was my first time to visit and I was thrilled to have a chance to explore the amazing food and mix of cultures. But of all the delicious street food in Hat Yai, there‚Äôs nothing more famous than Hat Yai Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà). Get ready for an ultimate fried chicken street food tour! #HatYai #Thailand #streetfood #friedchicken

When you mention fried chicken in Thailand, immediately people from the entire country will think about Hat Yai, and you can find Hat Yai style Thai fried chicken in pretty much every town and village throughout Thailand. There are a couple things to first know about this style of fried chicken. Number one is that it‚Äôs usually a very light batter - not bready. The marinade often includes some Thai spices like coriander seed and roots, pepper, and sometimes milk. The chicken is fried so all the golden crispiness is coating the meat rather than on the breading. Next, Hat Yai Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà) is almost always eaten with sticky rice. Finally, it would not be Hat Yai Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà) without crispy fried shallots. That combination is what makes it what it is, and it‚Äôs crazy good.

Here are the places we ate:

Laila Fried Chicken (‡∏£‡πâ‡∏≤‡∏ô‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡πÑ‡∏•‡∏•‡∏≤) - https://goo.gl/maps/xHiCisnySpvCXaKP8 - First we headed to this amazing street food stall for popular fried chicken, especially catering to students from the Prince of Songkhla University. Fried chicken was excellent, and they are extremely friendly.

Ba Sao Fried Chicken (‡∏õ‡πâ‡∏≤‡∏™‡∏≤‡∏ß‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡πÑ‡∏°‡πâ‡∏ü‡∏∑‡∏ô) - https://goo.gl/maps/akeF6xsgRYyYdDut8 - What‚Äôs especially cool about this old school fried chicken stall is they still cook over wood fire. The chicken is crispy and delicious.

Kaitod MEENA (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà‡∏°‡∏µ‡∏ô‡∏≤) - https://g.page/KaitodMeena?share - Located right at the main market in Hat Yai. I loved the biryani with fried chicken, and the owners are so friendly.

Sofeeya Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏ã‡∏≠‡∏ü‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏≤) - https://goo.gl/maps/vYQte8HeDSnw9DmC6 - This is some of the best fried chicken I‚Äôve ever had in my life. Very locally popular.

And that completes this ultimate Thai street food Hat Yai Fried Chicken (‡πÑ‡∏Å‡πà‡∏ó‡∏≠‡∏î‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏î‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏ç‡πà) tour. What a day of fried chicken!

snippet.title: Dune Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Beyond fear, destiny awaits. Watch the trailer for the highly anticipated #DuneMovie now. 


-----------------
https://www.facebook.com/dune
 https://twitter.com/dunemovie
https://www.instagram.com/dunemovie
-----------------

Oscar  nominee  Denis  Villeneuve  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049‚Äù)  directs  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary Pictures‚Äô ‚ÄúDune,‚Äù the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people.  As  malevolent  forces  explode  into conflict over the planet‚Äôs exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence‚Äîa commodity capable of unlocking humanity‚Äôs greatest potential‚Äîonly those who can conquer their fear will survive.The film stars Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name,‚Äù  ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson  (‚ÄúStephen  King‚Äôs  Doctor  Sleep,‚Äù   ‚ÄúMission:  Impossible  ‚Äì  Fallout‚Äù),  Oscar  Isaac  (the ‚ÄúStar  Wars‚Äù franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúMilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Infinity War‚Äù), Stellan Skarsg√•rd (HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúChernobyl,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Endgame‚Äù), Stephen McKinley Henderson (‚ÄúFences,‚Äù ‚ÄúLady Bird‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Chang Chen (‚ÄúMr.  Long,‚Äù ‚ÄúCrouching  Tiger,  Hidden  Dragon‚Äù),    David  Dastmalchian  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Dark  Knight‚Äù), Sharon  Duncan-Brewster  (‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story,‚Äù  Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúSex  Education‚Äù),   with  Oscar  nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), with Jason Momoa (‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúGame of Thrones‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúSkyfall‚Äù).   Villeneuve directed ‚ÄúDune‚Äù from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert.  Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter  and  Joe  Caracciolo,  Jr.   The  executive  producers  are  Tanya  Lapointe,  Joshua  Grode,  Herbert  W.  Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert. Behind  the  scenes,  Villeneuve  reteamed  with  two-time  Oscar-nominated  production  designer  Patrice  Vermette  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúSicario,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Young  Victoria‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-nominated  editor  Joe  Walker  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚Äú12  Years  a  Slave‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-winning  visual  effects  supervisor  Paul  Lambert  (‚ÄúFirst Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù).    He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù  ‚ÄúZero  Dark  Thirty,‚Äù  ‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story‚Äù);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  
Jacqueline West (‚ÄúThe Revenant,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,‚Äù ‚ÄúQuills‚Äù) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúInception‚Äù).  Oscar-winning and multiple  Oscar-nominated  composer  Hans  Zimmer  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúInception,‚Äù  ‚ÄúGladiator,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Lion King‚Äù) is creating the score.  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary  Pictures  Present  ‚ÄúDune.‚Äù    The  film  is  slated  to  be  released  in  theaters on December 18, 2020.

snippet.title: Reporter investigates her own father's death in Australia's rural hospitals | 60 Minutes Australia
snippet.description:
Subscribe here: http://9Soci.al/chmP50wA97J Full Episodes: https://9now.app.link/uNP4qBkmN6 | The Greatest Loss (2020)

In a very special edition of 60 MINUTES, Liz Hayes reports on what is the most important, and personal, story of her career. However, it‚Äôs also a story that in modern Australia she shouldn‚Äôt need to tell. It‚Äôs about decent people in the country who are dying because of a rural health system that's broken and failing them. They are people like Liz‚Äôs precious dad. For many years Bryan Ryan was a farmer who lived near Taree, north of Newcastle in NSW. He was 88 years old when he died a year ago, but it‚Äôs highly likely he‚Äôd still be alive today if not for a catastrophic medical error that occurred while he was being treated in the rural health system.  As Liz reveals, what happened to her dad, Bryan Ryan, is inexcusable but it's just one of many cases that are as heart-breaking as they are tragic.

WATCH more of 60 Minutes Australia: https://www.60minutes.com.au 
LIKE 60 Minutes Australia on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/60Minutes9 
FOLLOW 60 Minutes Australia on Twitter: https://twitter.com/60Mins 
FOLLOW 60 Minutes Australia on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/60minutes9

For forty years, 60 Minutes have been telling Australians the world‚Äôs greatest stories. Tales that changed history, our nation and our lives. Reporters Liz Hayes, Tom Steinfort, Tara Brown, Liam Bartlett and Sarah Abo look past the headlines because there is always a bigger picture. Sundays are for 60 Minutes.

snippet.description:
UFC middleweight champion Israel Adesanya joins Ariel Helwani‚Äôs MMA Show to preview his title fight vs. Paulo Costa. Adesanya describes what it was like to live and train at City Kickboxing for the bout, and looks back at (6:03) the verbal altercation he had with Costa on SportsCenter. ‚ÄúThe Last Stylebender‚Äù says (11:30) it‚Äôs not personal between them, that it‚Äôs just business. (18:14) Adesanya explains why he‚Äôs rooting for Jared Cannonier in his UFC 254 matchup vs. Robert Whittaker and (20:08) how he‚Äôs feeling over a week out from UFC 253.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Fulham vs Arsenal (0-3) | Willian, Gabriel impress on debuts
snippet.description:
We got off to a flying start in the Premier League with a classy performance and three points at Craven Cottage.

Alex Lacazette, debutant Gabriel and Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang were on target while the outstanding Willian claimed two assists on his first appearance for us.

Fulham were bright in the opening moments and a misjudgement from Gabriel almost let in Aboubakar Kamara. Bernd Leno did well to claw the ball off his toes.

From then on, the home side could not live with our pace, movement and quality.

The first goal was a scrappy one. Mohamed Elneny found Aubameyang and his cutback was fired goalwards by Granit Xhaka. Tim Ream failed to clear, Willian reacted first to force a save from Marek Rodak and Lacazette tucked away the rebound.

Willian struck a free-kick against the base of a post with Rodak beaten, and Aubameyang almost scored from a trademark burst in behind the defence in the left-hand channel.

Gabriel grew in stature as the game unfolded and he marked his debut with a downward header to convert Willian's corner. That effectively put the match to bed very early in the second half.

After that it was a matter of how many we would score, and Aubameyang got the third and final goal thanks to a delightful crossfield pass from Willian and one of the captain's sumptuous finishes into the far corner.

There will be tougher tests ahead, but this was a hugely-encouraging start to the new campaign.

#arsenal #arsenalhighlights #willian #aubameyang #gabrielMagalhaes

ABOUT ARSENAL FC


Arsenal Football Club were formed in 1886. They have amassed 13 League titles, 14 FA Cups and many other major trophies since then. Their greatest players include: Thierry Henry, Dennis Bergkamp, Tony Adams, Ian Wright, Robert Pires, Liam Brady, Patrick Vieira, Cliff Bastin and Charlie George.

snippet.title: I Tried Acrylic Pour Art For The First Time
snippet.description:
Hello friends! Apologies for the long absence, but we are trying to get things back on track. No, this video didn‚Äôt take us 3 months to make - we filmed a bunch of videos in July and this is the first of them to be released! It‚Äôs not a magnum opus, just supposed to be fun and lighthearted. If you want to read more about our plans, you can check out my blog post here:

https://www.safiyasnewintrosong.com/single-post/2020/09/04/where-have-we-been

Now, onto the video! A few weeks ago, somewhere deep in a visual ASMR YouTube rabbit hole, I discovered the online acrylic pour art community - where people essentially make interesting color combos of paint in a cup, then pour that cup onto a canvas or object - and then manipulate that object to create truly mesmerizing, rainbow, psychedelic pieces of art. And I was instantly hooked - just something about the way the paints flow from the cup and then slide around the canvas really got me, ya know? So I decided to pick an acrylic pour art video and try to follow it myself, to see if I could do it too. So I chose a "pouring guru", Tiktus color art, and got to work.

What do you guys think of my ~acrylic pouring adventure~?

This video is NOT sponsored!!

Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/
Twitter: https://twitter.com/safiyajn
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/safnygaard/

The tutorial we followed is here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yndPwAMGEgg
You can check out Tiktus‚Äôs channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCeAvBShy5a2_vTFflQG_zWg

MUSIC
Via AudioNetwork

snippet.title: MAX - Blueberry Eyes (feat. SUGA of BTS) [Official Music Video]
snippet.description:
MAX ‚Äì Blueberry Eyes (feat. SUGA of BTS) [Official Music Video]

Stream: https://orcd.co/blueberryeyes 
Spotify: http://open.spotify.com/album/2dEJHnsuxIij7YeBbt0sVm
Apple: https://music.apple.com/us/album/colour-vision/1524457751?ls=1

Bringing this music video to life has been such a special experience. I wanted it to feel as if Disney magically made a baby with Wes Anderson in the world of Colour Vision with every bit of our souls intertwined. Emily is my actual wife and she is really pregnant right now with our first child, so art imitates life in a fun way with this video. We studied and memorized all of the Korean lyrics to Suga‚Äôs incredible and romantic verse and all of the blueberries in the bathtub ended up being reused to create limited edition blueberry dyed blueberry eyes shirts. This video is a piece of our hearts and I hope it sparks the same magic in you viewing it as it did for us creating it. Thank you to Suga for being so brilliant on this song and more importantly for being a wonderful friend. Much love.

snippet.title: Detransition: F√ºr sie war die Geschlechtsangleichung der falsche Weg | reporter
snippet.description:
üë©üèºüßëüèºüë©üèº Nele ist detrans. Das bedeutet: Sie hatte eine Transition, also eine Geschlechtsangleichung ‚Äì nicht nur durch Testosteron, sondern auch mit einer Operation. So wurde aus Nele Transmann Peer. Dann merkte sie aber, dass die Geschlechtsangleichung f√ºr sie doch nicht der richtige Weg war. Heute ist sie wieder Nele und definiert sich nicht mehr als transgender.

üè• Lisa begleitet Nele zu der Klinik, in der sie eine geschlechtsangleichende OP hatte und reist mit ihr in ihre Vergangenheit. Nele erz√§hlt, wie sie √ºberhaupt auf den Gedanken kam, trans zu sei, wie sie ihren Namen √§ndern lie√ü und wieso sie heute sagt: Ich bin nicht mehr transgender. Au√üerdem treffen die beiden Neles Freundin Ellie. Sie hat sich schon als Jugendliche einer Transition unterzogen, lebt heute - mit 21 - aber auch wieder als Frau. 

üé∂ Musik:
Mac Miller - Rain

ü§î Wie viele junge Menschen brechen ihre Geschlechtsangleichung ab oder wollen sie r√ºckg√§ngig machen? Zu diesem Thema gibt es wenige Studien, vor allem Langzeitbeobachtungen fehlen. Denn erst seit wenigen Jahren haben junge Menschen, die trans sind, √ºberhaupt erst die M√∂glichkeit, entsprechende Ma√ünahmen zu ergreifen. Es gibt daher keine verl√§ssliche Zahl dazu, wie viele Detransitioner es in Deutschland gibt. 

üë©üèº‚Äç‚öñÔ∏èüë®üèº‚Äç‚öñÔ∏è Der deutsche Ethikrat hat sich im Februar 2020 mit √Ñrz*tinnen, Therapeut*innen und Betroffenen zum Thema Transidentit√§t bei Kindern und Jugendlichen ausgetauscht. In der daraus entstandenen Ad-hoc-Empfehlung hei√üt es: ‚ÄûDie Ursachen des deutlichen Anstiegs der Zahl der Behandlungs- und Beratungssuchenden, unter diesen ein hoher Anteil von (nach ihrem Geburtsgeschlecht) weiblichen Jugendlichen, sind umstritten und bed√ºrfen dringend weiterer Kl√§rung. Auch die langfristigen Auswirkungen medizinischer Behandlungen m√ºssen weiter untersucht werden, um die schwierigen prognostischen Entscheidungen auf eine bessere empirische Basis zu stellen.‚Äú 

üåà Um aufzukl√§ren hat Nele mit ihrer Freundin Ellie zusammen das Projekt ‚ÄûPost trans‚Äú gegr√ºndet. Ihr findet es hier: https://post-trans.com

üì≤ In dem Film werden Essst√∂rungen und Depressionen erw√§hnt. Wenn es dir nicht gut geht, findest du hier Hilfe: 

- Unter 0800/111 0 111 und 0800/ 111 0 222 und 0800/ 116 123 k√∂nnt ihr anonym, kostenlos und jederzeit die Telefonseelsorge erreichen. 
- Kinder und Jugendliche erreichen unter  0800 - 111 0 333 montags bis samstags von 14 bis 20 Uhr die ‚ÄûNummer gegen Kummer‚Äú.
- Alternativ stehen euch auch per Mail oder Chat Seelsorger*innen zur Seite: https://online.telefonseelsorge.de/

Die Stellungnahme des Ethikrats und die Aussagen verschiedener Expert*innen zum Thema findet ihr hier: 
https://www.ethikrat.org/forum-bioethik/trans-identitaet-bei-kindern-und-jugendlichen-therapeutische-kontroversen-ethische-fragen/?cookieLevel=accept-all&fbclid=IwAR2UvvB9N9AAzxMxx9Beh0LHgojRT4DcSjdg6D_d9GAgvmB8_4Xxo3QfzMM&cHash=9761029a8a03a9962e065078e3ab4aac

üìÉ In diesem Artikel wird noch mal genauer erl√§utert, warum die Studienlage so schwierig ist: https://acamh.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/camh.12361


üéû Team: Lisa Altmeier, Julian Guttzeit, Lukas Hellbr√ºgge, Andreas Josef, Julia von Cube

üëâ Ihr findet uns auch hier: 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/reporter
Facebook: http://facebook.com/reporter.offiziell/
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/reporter.offiziell/
Snapchat: https://www.snapchat.com/discover/Reporter/3246991136

üëâ #reporter geh√∂rt zu #funk:
YouTube: http://youtube.com/funkofficial
funk Web-App: http://go.funk.net
Facebook: http://facebook.com/funk

‚òùÔ∏è Oft sind Meinung und Subjektivit√§t alles: Wir aber legen Wert auf Recherche, Transparenz, Unvorein-genommenheit und Relevanz. Wir sind mutig, unideologisch und ergebnisoffen. Meinung machen andere. Wir machen Journalismus. Jeden Mittwoch, 16:30 Uhr gibt es eine neue Folge f√ºr euch.

üë©üèº Ich bin Lisa Altmeier und ich habe erst Medienpsychologie in K√∂ln studiert und dann die Deutsche Journalistenschule in M√ºnchen besucht. Nachdem ich meinen eigenen Kanal Crowdspondent gestartet habe, bin ich bei PULS Reportage und dann bei reporter gelandet. Ich recherchiere besonders gerne Themen, die euch wichtig sind. Schreibt mir, wenn ihr Ideen habt oder auf ein Problem aufmerksam machen wollt.

üåà Um aufzukl√§ren hat Nele mit ihrer Freundin Ellie zusammen das Projekt ‚ÄûPost trans‚Äú gegr√ºndet. Ihr findet es hier: https://post-trans.com

üì≤ In dem Film werden Essst√∂rungen und Depressionen erw√§hnt. Wenn es dir nicht gut geht, findest du hier Hilfe: 

- Unter 0800/111 0 111 und 0800/ 111 0 222 und 0800/ 116 123 k√∂nnt ihr anonym, kostenlos und jederzeit die Telefonseelsorge erreichen. 
- Kinder und Jugendliche erreichen unter  0800 - 111 0 333 montags bis samstags von 14 bis 20 Uhr die ‚ÄûNummer gegen Kummer‚Äú.
- Alternativ stehen euch auch per Mail oder Chat Seelsorger*innen zur Seite: https://online.telefonseelsorge.de/

Die Stellungnahme des Ethikrats und die Aussagen verschiedener Expert*innen zum Thema findet ihr hier: 
https://www.ethikrat.org/forum-bioethik/trans-identitaet-bei-kindern-und-jugendlichen-therapeutische-kontroversen-ethische-fragen/?cookieLevel=accept-all&fbclid=IwAR2UvvB9N9AAzxMxx9Beh0LHgojRT4DcSjdg6D_d9GAgvmB8_4Xxo3QfzMM&cHash=9761029a8a03a9962e065078e3ab4aac

üìÉ In diesem Artikel wird noch mal genauer erl√§utert, warum die Studienlage so schwierig ist: https://acamh.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/camh.12361


üéû Team: Lisa Altmeier, Julian Guttzeit, Lukas Hellbr√ºgge, Andreas Josef, Julia von Cube

‚òùÔ∏è Oft sind Meinung und Subjektivit√§t alles: Wir aber legen Wert auf Recherche, Transparenz, Unvorein-genommenheit und Relevanz. Wir sind mutig, unideologisch und ergebnisoffen. Meinung machen andere. Wir machen Journalismus. Jeden Mittwoch, 16:30 Uhr gibt es eine neue Folge f√ºr euch.

üë©üèº Ich bin Lisa Altmeier und ich habe erst Medienpsychologie in K√∂ln studiert und dann die Deutsche Journalistenschule in M√ºnchen besucht. Nachdem ich meinen eigenen Kanal Crowdspondent gestartet habe, bin ich bei PULS Reportage und dann bei reporter gelandet. Ich recherchiere besonders gerne Themen, die euch wichtig sind. snippet.title: The Mandalorian | Season 2 Official Trailer | Disney+
snippet.description:
The new season of The Mandalorian starts streaming Friday, October 30, only on Disney+. 

The Mandalorian and the Child continue their journey, facing enemies and rallying allies as they make their way through a dangerous galaxy in the tumultuous era after the collapse of the Galactic Empire. ‚ÄúThe Mandalorian‚Äù stars Pedro Pascal, Gina Carano, Carl Weathers and Giancarlo Esposito. Directors for the new season include Jon Favreau, Dave Filoni, Bryce Dallas Howard, Rick Famuyiwa, Carl Weathers, Peyton Reed and Robert Rodriguez. Showrunner Jon Favreau serves as executive producer along with Dave Filoni, Kathleen Kennedy and Colin Wilson, with Karen Gilchrist serving as co-executive producer.
